text: Kuwait's fourth district consists of 18 large residential areas extending from Farwaniya to Jahra. Other major residential areas include Ardhiya, Sabah Al- Nasser, Firdous, Omariya, Rabiya, Jleeb Al-Shuyoukh and Andalus. It is the second largest district in terms of the number of voters with 93,711 eligible voters, with women forming 58 percent of the electorate with 54,351 voters and 39,360 males. thumb Category:Geography of Kuwait
title: Kuwait's Fourth District
